      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the sponge, 28 to 32 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 170°C fan. Grease and line two 20 cm round cake tins. Rub the {{orange}} zest into the {{caster-sugar}} with your fingertips until fragrant. Beat in the {{unsalted-butter}} until pale and fluffy. Add the {{eggs}} one at a time, beating well after each. Sift together the {{plain-flour}}, {{cocoa-powder}}, {{baking-powder}}, and {{bicarbonate-of-soda}} and fold in two additions, adding the {{whole-milk}} with the second. Divide between the tins and bake for 28 to 32 minutes until a skewer comes out clean. Cool in tins for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a rack to cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the ganache and assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Place the {{dark-chocolate}} in a heatproof bowl. Heat the {{double-cream}} in a small saucepan until just beginning to simmer, then pour over the chocolate. Add the {{orange-juice}}. Leave for 2 minutes, then stir from the centre outward until smooth. This is a ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "ganache",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp71ifbb00003wv40s07762b"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ". Leave at room temperature for 20 to 30 minutes until it thickens to a pourable consistency. Place one sponge layer on a rack set over a tray. Spread 3 tablespoons of ganache over it, top with the second layer, and pour the remaining ganache over the top, letting it run down the sides naturally. Leave undisturbed for at least 30 minutes to set before cutting.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
